{
    "name": "Gravedigger",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Gravedigger",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 223",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 223",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 223
                }
            ],
            "html": "An often-overlooked group of laborers, gravediggers have a reputation for being as quiet and grim as their workplace. They are commonly strong and tough from their long hours of backbreaking labor, and they tend to have a unique perspective on life and death.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 15"
        },
        {
            "name": "Laborers",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Forced Labor",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 222",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 222",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 222
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Many creatures and societies still practice forced labor, whether through full enslavement or indebted labor to pay a society for their crimes. The <a aonid=\"913\" game-obj=\"NPCs\">dockhand</a>, <a aonid=\"914\" game-obj=\"NPCs\">farmer</a>, <a aonid=\"915\" game-obj=\"NPCs\">miner</a>, and <a aonid=\"912\" game-obj=\"NPCs\">servant</a> could also be forced laborers. Forced laborers could become allies or at least informants to PCs who free them."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Laborer Games",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 222",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 222",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 222
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Laborers tend to play games when the work is slow or while on break. Common games include Gremlin Row, which involves rolling dice and trying to match them, as well as Fishing with Fire, in which players try to get all the cards of one type from a deck without losing all of their own cards and getting \u201cburned.\u201d"
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 222",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 222",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 222
                }
            ],
            "html": "Every day, laborers perform backbreaking physical work."
        }
    ],
